        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Rename provider server internals and APIs",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe built-in provider server implementations and public API names still carried `fake-server` / `fake-provider` wording. Inside Crabline that phrasing is redundant, and it made the package surface clunky now that these are first-class local provider servers.\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Moved internal server implementations from `src/fake-servers` to `src/servers`.\n- Renamed public server APIs/types to names like `startSlackServer`, `StartedSlackServer`, `CrablineServerManifest`, and `startCrablineServer`.\n- Renamed OpenClaw bridge helpers from `*FakeProvider*` to `*Provider*`.\n- Updated server test filenames, docs, CLI copy, changelog wording, and banner wording to use local provider/server terminology.\n- Changed default recorder/artifact paths from fake-provider/fake-server names to provider/server names.\n\n## Breaking Change\n\nThis intentionally removes the old clunky exported names. OpenClaw will be updated in lockstep against the new Crabline package version.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm verify`\n  - 34 test files passed\n  - 164 tests passed\n",
